-- Honda: Thai floods to cut 2011/12 shipments by 260,000 cars
-- 
-- Tue Jan 31, 2012 1:42am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/01/31/us-honda-sales-idUSTRE80U0AK20120131

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Honda Motor Co estimates that last autumn's Thai floods will cut its global shipments by 260,000 cars in the financial year ending in March, Chief Financial Officer Fumihiko Ike told reporters. 
 Honda posted a 65 percent slide in quarterly operating profit on Tuesday. The floods inundated its plant in Thailand in early October. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim ; Editing by  Chris Gallagher )